LittlevGL
#########

Origin:
   LittlevGL - Open-source Embedded GUI Library
   https://littlevgl.com/

Status:
   Version 5.2-rc

Purpose:
   Embedded graphics library

Description:

   General Description (from projects website):
   "LittlevGL is a free and open-source graphics library providing everything
   you need to create embedded GUI with easy-to-use graphical elements,
   beautiful visual effects and low memory footprint."

   Problem:
   Rendering objects to a screen

   Why this package:
   Lightweight well maintained graphics library.
   Requested in issue #6709

Dependencies:
   No external run time dependencies.
   Dependency towards tools to generate c arrays for fonts and images.

   Library depends on Zephyr k_malloc & k_free.

   Zephyr will directly depend on the API provided by the library and no
   abstraction layer is available.

URL:
   Home: https://littlevgl.com/
   Source: https://github.com/littlevgl/lvgl

